title: Historic Downtown1 Bdrm Apt.
posting_body: ["In the late 1940's the John and Lydia  Comstock Estate was converted into one bedroom apartments.", ' From the photos you can see that the restoration done by the current owner has returned these units back to the original beauty.', 'The St Croix River and Swimming beach is located just down the Street.', "Lakefront Park and Historic Downtown Hudson's, Bars, Restaurants and Shops, are close and easy to walk too.", 'This Historic Home sits on over 1/2 of a city block, located in the heart of the Historic district .', 'Wooded lot with lots of privacy.', 'Off street private parking area behind the property for tenants only.', 'Ample street parking for  Visitors out front on Vine Street year round.', ' Coin operated Washer and dryer on site.', ' New energy efficient furnaces with on-demand water and set back thermostats in this well insulated, completely restored  apartments allow you to control your energy consumption, and ensure you will always have the amount of hot water you require.', ' Beautiful natural wood floors and woodwork throughout the apartment have all been refinished.', ' Beautifully decorated with Bradbury and Bradbury screen-print papers through out.', 'Exceptional Sunset views every evening over the St Croix River can be seen from your private deck  I pay the water utility bill and normal trash and recycling bill.', '  You pay the Xcel-energy bill for gas and electric.', ' This is not your normal apartment living.', ' You will be living in one of the oldest Historic homes in Hudson, suitable to single, quiet and respectful professional adults, who care about and respect the other residents and landlords well being along with their own.', 'NO PETS..', 'NO SMOKING inside building.', 'NO DRUG use by tenants or their guests.', 'No ALCOHOL ABUSE by tenants or their guests.', 'I want everyone who lives here to feel safe, and have a stress free environment to come home to.', 'This home is not a hangout or party place for you and your friends, and violators will not only have their lease terminated but they will also forfeit their damage deposit.', 'Rent is $1000 per month.', ' Available Aug 1  send text or call  PATT at', 'show contact info', 'between the hours of noon to 10pm only, if you are a qualified applicant for this unique property, and wish to set up an appointment.', ' Thank You.', '804 Vine St,
